solution: If we subtract 4 from all three expressions we get  \[-6<3x<-2.\] Dividing by 3 gives  \[-2<x<-\frac23.\] The only integer in this range is $-1$.  Therefore there is only $\boxed{1}$ integral solution.
model_solution:
Step 1: Subtract 4 from all three parts of the inequality.

$-6<3x<-6$
Step 2: Divide all three parts of the inequality by 3.

$-2<x<-2$
Step 3:
$-2 < x < -2$

This is the same as $-2 < x < -2$, which is not an inequality since the same value is given for $x$.  Therefore, there are no integers that satisfy the inequality.

Final Answer.
